{"id": 225050016, "title": "Search for 2,000 missing people underway in landslide-hit Papua New Guinea \u2013 The Frontier Post", "text": "(AA): Rescue and search operations in Papua New Guinea continued Wednesday to locate 2,000 missing persons after the nation was hit by devastating landslides in Enga province. People are using \u201cshovels, sticks and their bare hands to identify bodies and survivors,\u201d ABC News reported. Residential areas were hit by landslides at around 3:00 a.m. (1700GMT Thursday) on Friday, burying homes, infrastructure and farmland under up to eight meters of soil and debris. To aid rescue efforts, Australia has dispatched two aircraft with emergency supplies, in addition to a 16-strong team of disaster relief specialists to assist the recovery efforts. International Organization for Migration (IOM) said the incident was \u201cone of the deadliest disasters in the country\u2019s recent history.\u201d Thousands of people have lost their homes and belongings in \u201cthe blink of an eye,\u201d said Serhan Aktoprak, IOM chief of mission in Papua New Guinea, adding: \u201cThe scale of this disaster is truly heartbreaking.\u201d He said more than 150 houses were buried in Yambali village alone.", "summary": "<img width=\"810\" height=\"456\" src=\"https://thefrontierpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/thumbs_b_c_dc5646e4fdbe45d6960840f9e4692411.jpg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15px;\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://thefrontierpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/thumbs_b_c_dc5646e4fdbe45d6960840f9e4692411.jpg 864w, https://thefrontierpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/thumbs_b_c_dc5646e4fdbe45d6960840f9e4692411-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thefrontierpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/thumbs_b_c_dc5646e4fdbe45d6960840f9e4692411-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thefrontierpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/thumbs_b_c_dc5646e4fdbe45d6960840f9e4692411-810x456.jpg 810w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 8